Interface IterableStreamable<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<T>, SplitableIterable<T>, Streamable<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    JImmutableArray<T>, JImmutableList<T>, JImmutableListMap<K,V>, JImmutableMap<K,V>, JImmutableMultiset<T>, JImmutableRandomAccessList<T>, JImmutableSet<T>, JImmutableSetMap<K,V>, JImmutableStack<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractJImmutableArray, AbstractJImmutableListMap, AbstractJImmutableMap, AbstractJImmutableMultiset, AbstractJImmutableSet, AbstractJImmutableSetMap, CursorStreamable, EmptyHashMap, EntryIterableStreamable, JImmutableArrayList, JImmutableBtreeList, JImmutableHashListMap, JImmutableHashMap, JImmutableHashMultiset, JImmutableHashSet, JImmutableHashSetMap, JImmutableInsertOrderListMap, JImmutableInsertOrderMap, JImmutableInsertOrderMultiset, JImmutableInsertOrderSet, JImmutableInsertOrderSetMap, JImmutableLinkedStack, JImmutableTemplateSetMap, JImmutableTreeListMap, JImmutableTreeMap, JImmutableTreeMultiset, JImmutableTreeSet, JImmutableTreeSetMap, JImmutableTrieArray, TransformStreamable

    public interface IterableStreamable<T>
extends SplitableIterable<T>, Streamable<T>
    Interface for classes that can produce java.util.Streams and are also Iterable. The default stream creation implementations use spliterator().

      • partition

        default <C extends Insertable<T,C>> IterableStreamable.Partitions<C> partition(@Nonnull
                                                                               C matched,
                                                                               @Nonnull
                                                                               C unmatched,
                                                                               @Nonnull
                                                                               java.util.function.Predicate<T> predicate)
        Apply the predicate to all elements in iterator order and add the elements to the specified collections based on predicate return value. All elements for which predicate returns true are added to matched. All others are added to unmatched. Resulting collections are packaged into Partitions object and returned.
        Parameters:
        matched - collection to accumulate the matched elements
        unmatched - collection to accumulate the unmatched elements
        predicate - predicate applied to each element
        Returns:
        Partitions containing (matched,unmatched)

      • reduce

        default Holder<T> reduce(Func2<T,T,T> accumulator)
        Apply the specified accumulator to all elements in iterator order calling the accumulator function for each element. The first call to accumulator is passed the first element in the sequence. All remaining calls to accumulator are passed the result from the previous call.
        Parameters:
        accumulator - method called to compute result
        Returns:
        empty Holder if the sequence is empty, otherwise Holder containing result from last call to accumulator
